  <main class="container">
    <section class="hero">
      <h1>What is Eddy Current Pulsed Thermography (ECPT)</h1>
      <p class="sub">
        A short technical introduction to principles, instrumentation, and typical inspection workflow.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="panel">
      <div class="panel-head">
        <h2>Overview</h2>
        <p class="muted">
          ECPT combines electromagnetic induction with infrared thermography to reveal subsurface features through transient thermal contrast.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="info-grid">
        <div class="info-card">
          <h3>Working principle</h3>
          <p>Induced eddy currents generate Joule heating; defects and material inhomogeneity perturb current flow and heat diffusion.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="info-card">
          <h3>Typical system</h3>
          <p>Excitation (coil + power), control/synchronisation, infrared camera, and scanning/positioning as required.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="info-card">
          <h3>Why ECPT for composites</h3>
          <p>Non-contact thermal sensing with fast area coverage, with modelling needed to handle anisotropy, curvature, and layered structures.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="panel">
      <div class="panel-head">
        <h2>Inspection workflow</h2>
        <p class="muted">A high-level pipeline from excitation to interpretation (no equations).</p>
      </div>

      <ol class="muted" style="line-height: 1.8;">
        <li>Define the inspection target and expected defect types.</li>
        <li>Design excitation (frequency, pulse, coil geometry) and measurement setup.</li>
        <li>Acquire thermal sequence and auxiliary signals (if available).</li>
        <li>Pre-process data (registration, denoising, normalisation).</li>
        <li>Extract features (transient contrast, phase-like metrics, model-based inversion).</li>
        <li>Validate against reference samples and complementary NDT methods.</li>
      </ol>
    </section>

    <section class="panel">
      <div class="panel-head">
        <h2>Placeholders for figures</h2>
        <p class="muted">You can insert diagrams later.</p>
      </div>

